<p><a name="Further_reading" id="Further_reading"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Art_theft&amp;action=edit&amp;section=36" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFDolnick.2C_Edward2005"><a href="/wiki/Edward_Dolnick" title="Edward Dolnick">Dolnick, Edward</a> (2005). <i>The Rescue Artist: A True Story of Art, Thieves, and the Hunt for a Missing Masterpiece</i>. HarperCollins. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780060531171" class="internal">ISBN 978-0060531171</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Rescue+Artist%3A+A+True+Story+of+Art%2C+Thieves%2C+and+the+Hunt+for+a+Missing+Masterpiece&amp;rft.aulast=Dolnick%2C+Edward&amp;rft.au=Dolnick%2C+Edward&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.pub=HarperCollins&amp;rft.isbn=978-0060531171&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Art_theft"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> A detailed account of the recovery of Munch's <i>The Scream</i> after it was stolen from the National Gallery in Oslo in 1994.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFMcShane.2C_Thomas.2C_with_Dary_Matera2007">McShane, Thomas, with Dary Matera (2007). <i>Loot: Inside the World of Stolen Art</i>. <a href="/wiki/Maverick_House_Publishers" title="Maverick House Publishers">Maverick House Publishers</a>. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781905379378" class="internal">ISBN 978-1905379378</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Loot%3A+Inside+the+World+of+Stolen+Art&amp;rft.aulast=McShane%2C+Thomas%2C+with+Dary+Matera&amp;rft.au=McShane%2C+Thomas%2C+with+Dary+Matera&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BMaverick+House+Publishers%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=978-1905379378&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Art_theft"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFReit.2C_Seymour1981"><a href="/wiki/Seymour_Reit" title="Seymour Reit">Reit, Seymour</a> (1981). <i>The Day They Stole the Mona Lisa</i>. Summit Books. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780671250560" class="internal">ISBN 978-0671250560</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Day+They+Stole+the+Mona+Lisa&amp;rft.aulast=Reit%2C+Seymour&amp;rft.au=Reit%2C+Seymour&amp;rft.date=1981&amp;rft.pub=Summit+Books&amp;rft.isbn=978-0671250560&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Art_theft"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFNicholas.2C_Lynn1995"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Lynn_Nicholas&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Lynn Nicholas (page does not exist)">Nicholas, Lynn</a> (1995). <i>The Rape of Europa: The Fate of Europe's Treasures in the Third Reich and the Second World War</i>. Vintage. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780679756866" class="internal">ISBN 978-0679756866</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Rape+of+Europa%3A+The+Fate+of+Europe%27s+Treasures+in+the+Third+Reich+and+the+Second+World+War&amp;rft.aulast=Nicholas%2C+Lynn&amp;rft.au=Nicholas%2C+Lynn&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.pub=Vintage&amp;rft.isbn=978-0679756866&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Art_theft"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
